article.description: James Batemon had 19 points as Loyola Marymount got past Pacific 63-56 on Saturday.
article.headline: Batemon leads Loyola Marymount past Pacific 63-56
article.linkText: Batemon leads Loyola Marymount past Pacific 63-56
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- James Batemon had 19 points as Loyola Marymount got past Pacific 63-56 on Saturday. Dameane Douglas had 11 points for Loyola Marymount (18-10, 6-8 West Coast Conference). Eli Scott added seven assists. Roberto Gallinat scored a season-high 31 points for the Tigers (13-16, 3-11), whose losing streak reached five games. Jahlil Tripp added eight rebounds and six steals. The Lions improve to 2-0 against the Tigers this season. Loyola Marymount defeated Pacific 60-42 on Jan. 31. Loyola Marymount matches up against Santa Clara at home on Thursday. Pacific plays Gonzaga at home on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
